ce:section.ce:para:
Voltammetric measurements on bare and modified SPCEs were accomplished in a cell containing 10 mL phosphate buffer (optimized pH 7.5). The supporting electrolyte, phosphate buffer, was preferred to other buffers (borate and acetate) because the later resulted in an asymmetric current, presumably due to the sluggish oxidation of HU. All DPASV runs were recorded, implicating the standard addition method, in the potential window 0.0 - + 0.6 V with the analyte accumulation (t

                           acc
                        ) 90 s and accumulated potential (E

                           acc
                        ) - 0.1 V at the scan rate 10 mV s−1, pulse amplitude 25 mV, and pulse width 50 ms. CV runs were scanned in the same potential window as stated above, at various scan rates (20–200 mV s−1), in anodic stripping mode. The de-aeration of the cell content was not required in this work because DPASV runs were found to be identical in the presence and absence of oxygen. (The operating analytical conditions were optimized as described in Section S2 and Fig. S2).
